<h1>Problem 2232 - 2024 ELMOSL, G5, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 9</h2>
<p>Let \(ABC\) be a triangle with circumcenter \(O\) and circumcircle \(\omega\). Let \(D\) be the foot of the altitude from \(A\) to \(\overline{BC}\). Let \(P\) and \(Q\) be points on the circumcircles of triangles \(AOB\) and \(AOC\), respectively, such that \(A\), \(P\), and \(Q\) are collinear. Prove that if the circumcircle of triangle \(OPQ\) is tangent to \(\omega\) at \(T\), then \(\angle BTD=\angle CAP\).</p>
